sec.p:
Based on standardized Beta coefficients, Compression Resilience Rate and Graininess (handfeel properties), as well as Weight, were found to be the most influential properties, as they exhibited the highest absolute magnitudes after dimensionality reduction:


Compression Resilience Rate (absolute magnitude: 0.72) – rate at which the sample returns to its original shape or rate at which the sample opens after compression;

Fabric weight/unit area (absolute magnitude: 0.647);

Grainy (absolute magnitude: 0.376) – amount of small, round particles in the surface of the sample.
